text: Colten Sopp (born May 18, 1991) is an American professional wrestler. He currently wrestles for All Elite Wrestling (AEW) and competes under the ring name Colten Gunn and is one third of the current Unified World Trios Champions. He wrestles in a tag team called The Gunns with his real-life younger brother Austin. His father is professional wrestler Billy Gunn, who also wrestles in All Elite Wrestling. During his time in AEW, Gunn has been a one-time AEW World Tag Team Champion and Unified World Trios Champion. ==Career== ===All Elite Wrestling=== On the November 17, 2020 episode of Dark, Gunn would make his in-ring debut for All Elite Wrestling (AEW). He would join his father Billy Gunn and his brother Austin as The Gunn Club. They would defeat BSHP King, Joey Oâ€™Riley, and Sean Maluta. On the February 11, 2022 episode of Rampage, Colten and Austin would face Jurassic Express (Jungle Boy and Luchasaurus) for the AEW World Tag Team Championships but lost. On February 8, 2023 episode of Dynamite, The Gunn's would defeat The Acclaimed (Max Caster and Anthony Bowens) to win the AEW World Tag Team Championships. This was Austin's first championship in AEW. They would lose the titles to FTR (Dax Harwood and Cash Wheeler) on the April 5 episode of Dynamite in a Title vs. Career match. == References == == Other websites == * Category:1991 births Category:Living people Category:All Elite Wrestling people Category:American professional wrestlers Category:Sportspeople from Orlando, Florida
